The paper deals with the design of linear precoders/beamformers for signal superposition in NOMA multi-input multi-output multi-cellular systems to maximize the overall sum throughput subject to the users' QoS requirements. This involves optimization problems related to information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), multi-agent systems (cs.MM), and game theory (cs.GT). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
